thread.title: HS football stars of the week
thread.title_full: HS football stars of the week | Boston Herald

author: Herald Staff
title: HS football stars of the week
text:
DIVISION 1
• Doug Santos ran for 145 yards and two touchdowns as Peabody defeated Lynn Classical, 27-0.
• Nate Martino threw a touchdown pass in the fourth quarter to break a scoreless tie as Framingham snapped a 16-game losing streak with a 9-0 victory over Brookline.
• Kendrick Denose ran for 142 yards and two touchdowns on 26 carries, while adding a TD pass, as Methuen defeated Lawrence, 27-21.
DIVISION 2
•   Ryan Dauphinais rushed for 166 yards and two scores as Barnstable earned a 32-22 victory over Somerville.
• Justin Beck threw for 146 yards and three second-quarter touchdowns as unbeaten Billerica registered a 42-13 win over North Andover.
• Ethan McCu llough piled up 163 yards and three touchdowns as Lincoln-Sudbury cruised to a 43-8 victory over Cambridge.
DIVISION 3
• Ryan Reagan caught eight passes for 158 yards and two scores as Duxbury remained unbeaten in the Patriot Keenan with a 28-19 victory over Plymouth North.
•    John Williams caught 10 passes for 142 yards and four scores and Jake Dubbs had three interceptions in Medfield’s 28-7 win over Medway.
•   Alec Coleman ran for four scores and threw for a fifth as Arlington rallied to defeat Woburn, 34-33.
•   Liam Henning threw two touchdown passes in the final minute to lift Wayland over Masconomet, 14-7.
DIVISION 4
• Austin Ryan returned a punt 99 yards for a touchdown and caught five passes for 122 yards as Foxboro scored a 42-14 victory over Milford.
• James Eliason ran for 157 yards and three touchdowns as Bedford defeated Weston, 28-14.
• Justin Ireland rushed for 149 yards and a score as Norton blanked Bellingham, 14-0.
•   Brendan Patterson threw for 237 yards and three touchdowns as Westwood knocked off Millis-Hopedale, 20-6.
• Jake Ragusa rushed for 136 yards and two touchdowns in Canton’s 22-21 overtime win over Stoughton. He also recorded eight tackles and two sacks.
DIVISION 5
• Abraham Toe ran for 248 yards and four touchdowns on 20 carries as St. Mary’s defeated Archbishop Williams, 32-8.
•   Nick Landry rushed for 176 yards and a touchdown on 30 carries as Bishop Stang shut out Martha’s Vineyard, 13-0.
• Cory Bright completed 13-of-24 passes for 189 yards and four touchdowns, including the game-winner to Cody Mullen on the final play, as Bishop Fenwick edged Austin Prep, 26-21.
• Aidan Silva and Brendan Costa combined to rush for 341 yards and four touchdowns as Case defeated Bourne, 34-28.
DIVISION 6
• James LoChirco ran for 106 yards and scored twice as Mystic Valley bested Greater Lowell, 34-20.
•   Jay McClure’s 133 yards and two touchdowns on the ground propelled Bishop Connolly to a 34-0 rout of Southeastern.
• Deshaun Dias rushed for 210 yards and four touchdowns, becoming the school’s all-time scoring leader, as Mashpee defeated Hull, 42-20.
• Ivan Mertilus had another monster week, rushing for 252 yards and three touchdowns as St. Clement rolled over Matignon/St. Joseph’s, 46-0.
ISL/PREP
•  Thayer Academy earned its first win as Jamari Venter ran for 215 yards and four touchdowns on 23 carries in a 33-15 victory over Middlesex.
• Cam Macri rushed for four touchdowns as Governor’s Academy ran its record to 3-0 with a 41-27 victory over BB&N.
• Tyrell Wiggins scored five times in Dexter’s 42-7 victory over Kent’s Hill.
• Will Greer threw three touchdown passes as Roxbury Latin defeated St. Paul’s, 18-9.
